RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PHOEBE'S FROSTY went to the front, showed the way in the three path, responded well under heavy pressure in the stretch, shook off multiple foes into the final furlong and proved best under strong urging. REUNION TOUR saved ground on the first turn, prompted the pace, dropped back some near the eleven-sixteenths, was asked in the two path on the far turn, gained to make a bid inside of rivals in upper stretch, fought with the winner into the final furlong and was outfinished while clear for the place. MIDNIGHT EXPRESS went around the first turn in the two path, settled at the rear, was urged along late on the backstretch, chased four wide for most of the far turn then shifted five wide, gained to make an outside bid in upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened but just held the show. YOUR MISSION bumped lightly with an opponent at the start, went five wide on the first turn, settled just off the pace on the outside, made a bid late on the backstretch, vied in the four path around the far turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, dropped back into the final furlong and tired then just missed the show. UNCLE BRUCE broke out and bumped lightly with a foe, went three wide on the first turn, settled off the pace, was urged along passing the nine-sixteenths, traveled three wide around most of the far turn, shifted five wide late on that bend and failed to threaten. TIZA BROWN was rated in the two path on the first turn, settled down the backstretch, saved ground on the far turn, had the rider lose his crop inside the five-sixteenths and came up empty. BOINTHEBACK raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the pace down the backstretch, was urged along near the nine-sixteenths, dropped back three wide on the far turn and capitulated.

VIRADIA coaxed from the start, chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung four wide for home and tired. NEW YORK BANKER dueled early on and was shaken off into the turn, went three wide through the bend and continued three wide for home, then tired in the stretch.
